Reasoning: The problem of recognizing even hole free graphs is a graph theory problem, which is likely to fall under the categories of Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Computational Geometry (cs.CG), Graph Theory (cs.GT), and Computational Complexity (cs.CC). However, since the paper focuses on the algorithmic aspect of the problem, cs.DM and cs.DS are the most likely categories. The use of decomposition-based algorithms and the decomposition theorem of da Silva and Vuskovic also suggest that cs.CG and cs.GT are possible categories. Finally, the running time analysis of the algorithm indicates that the paper may also be relevant to the field of cs.CC.
